            <p>DR. S. H. SONNESCHEIN&#44;<lb/>
                RABBI OF CONGREGATION<lb/>
                SHAARE EMETH<lb/>
                Office&#58; In Temple&#44; corner Seventeenth and Pine Sts.<lb/></p>
            <p>St. Louis Mch 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1883<lb/></p>
                <p>Rev. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
                Philadelphia.<lb/>
                Rev. Sir &#38; Colleague&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>Your kind favor of &#91;Hebrew&#93; last reached me but this mor&#45;<lb/>ning&#44; and&#44; consequently&#44; too late for being of any direct bearing upon<lb/> my Editorial answer to your compliments paid to my humble self<lb/> in your dissertation on &#34;Spinozism&#34;.  My reply was already in the<lb/> hands of the typesetter by that time.  But rest assured&#44; my<lb/> dear &#38; Rev. Sir&#44; that it never entered my mind to think of<lb/> your difference of opinion and its expression in any other but<lb/> the most equitable sense.  The whole Literature on &#34;Spinoza&#34;<lb/> shows&#44; how often even the most cautious of Scholars and<lb/> thinkers were easily induced to do not exactly justice to the<lb/> &#34;martyred&#34; phenomenal philosopher.  Even his apparent parti&#45;<lb/>ality towards the Nazarene is yet under the cloud of prejudice&#59;<lb/> but anybody&#44; who makes a thorough study of his life&#44; charac&#44;<lb/>ter and writings&#44; will be bound to acknowledge&#44; that Spinoza&#44;<lb/> with all these seemingly strange leavings&#44; was a &#34;true Son of Israel&#34;<lb/> He was a &#91;Hebrew&#93; to the core&#44; and what more do we&#44; what more<lb/> can we expect of a Genius&#44; who&#44; deeper and farther than any one<lb/> before him&#44; penetrated into the &#34;Kosmos&#34; of mind &#43; matter &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#33;<lb/>  If&#44; not to accept the results of <hi rend="underline">true</hi> scientific criticism&#44; is the only<lb/> safe&#45;guard of piety&#44; then Mendelssohn too&#44; was an inveterate Infidel.<lb/>  Did he not write only a few hours before his departure from <hi rend="underline">this</hi> life&#63;<lb/>  &#34;I for my part remain loyal to my Jewish infidelity&#44; and would not depend even<lb/> upon an Arch&#45;Angel&#39;s Authority&#44; when Eternal truths are to be discussed&#33;&#34;&#95;&#95;<lb/>  More anon&#33;  Yours&#44; with all sincerity&#33;  S. H. Sonneschein.<lb/></p>
        </body>
